    detailedExplanationExpert: "Logical Fallacies - Informal Logic - This commits Argumentum ad Verecundiam with context-transfer error. Disaster rebuilding and proactive urban planning operate under fundamentally different constraints (emergency vs. long-term, resource-scarce vs. resource-available, post-crisis vs. preventive). The argument generalizes authority from one specific context (disaster response) to a universal urban planning claim, ignoring that the conditions of success in emergency rebuilding may not transfer to routine urban development.",
