    detailedExplanationExpert: "Logical Fallacies - Informal Logic - The Argumentum ad Popularity is particularly dangerous in financial contexts where mass participation can create bubbles. Widespread cryptocurrency adoption reflects speculative mania, media narratives, and social proof dynamics—not necessarily intrinsic value or sound investment principles. History is full of popular investments that ended catastrophically.",
