    detailedExplanationExpert: "Logical Fallacies - Informal Logic - The false dilemma (or false dichotomy) occurs when an argument presents exactly two alternatives as the only possibilities, when in fact additional options or gradations exist. Here the dichotomy of \"with us\" vs \"against us\" excludes neutrality, partial agreement, indifference, and conditional support. This rhetorical device is common in political and emotional contexts to force commitment.",
